---
description: Enforce English-only outputs and no emoji
alwaysApply: true
---

# Communication Standards

- Write all code in English.
- Write all code comments in English.
- Write all implementation instructions in English.
- Do not use emoji in code, comments, commit messages, documentation, or chat responses.
- If a requirement is unclear, ask concise clarification questions.
- Keep responses concise and implementation-focused.
- Treat all secrets as sensitive and never commit them.
- Ensure all secret-bearing files are covered by `.gitignore`.
- Before any push, run a push-safety review:
  - Check staged files for accidental secrets.
  - Block push if `.env`, keys, tokens, or credentials are included.
  - Ask user confirmation only after safety checks pass.
